  "title": "Senior Public Relations Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Overview</strong></p><p>This role drives Pazzion’s PR and Influencer Marketing initiatives across Singapore and regional markets, strengthening brand visibility, reputation, and engagement through effective media relations, influencer partnerships, and brand storytelling.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p>•\tPlan and execute PR and influencer strategies aligned with brand and campaign objectives</p><p>•\tManage media relations, press releases, media kits, and brand announcements</p><p>•\tLead end-to-end influencer and KOL collaborations, including sourcing, briefing, negotiations, deliverables, and performance tracking</p><p>•\tBuild and maintain relationships with media, influencers, agencies, and creators</p><p>•\tSupport and coordinate media events, product launches, store openings, and brand activations</p><p>•\tMonitor media coverage, social sentiment, and campaign performance, and provide insights and reports</p><p>•\tSupport brand reputation management and communications as required</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>•\tDiploma or Degree in Marketing, Communications, PR, or related fields</p><p>•\t3–5 years’ experience in PR, influencer marketing, or brand communications (fashion / retail / lifestyle preferred)</p><p>•\tStrong media and influencer network with solid writing and communication skills</p><p>•\tAble to manage PR and influencer initiatives independently with minimal supervision</p><p>•\tOrganized, proactive, and comfortable working in a fast-paced environment</p><p>•\tCandidates with stronger experience may be considered for an Assistant Manager role</p><p></p>",
